During inspection, found active coolant leaking. Pressure tested
cooling system, Found the coolant pump leaking, coolant is leaking from
weep hole. Removed air pipe to gain access to components, removed
throttle valve and drained the cooling system, removed coolant
reservoir and coolant pipes to gain access to coolant pump/thermostat
assembly. Removed toothed belt cover, removed the coolant
pump/thermostat assembly. Cleaned surrounding area. Installed new
thermostat assembly as per customer approval, installed new coolant
pump, installed with new gasket, with new hardware and connection
joirt Reinstalled throttle valve and other components Vacuum filled
cooling system. Scanned vehicle for faults, no faults present,
performed thermostat adaptation as per GFF test plan Test drove
vehicle to verify repairs. Vehicle is no longer leaking coolant at this
time.
